> > > > delayed_fput_lists nearly twice as fast they are retired by a singl=
e
> > > > work-queue thread running delayed_fput().  As you might imagine thi=
s
> > > > does not end well (20 million files in the queue at the time a snap=
shot
> > > > was taken for analysis).
> > > >=20
> > > > While this might point to a problem with the filesystem not handlin=
g the
> > > > final close efficiently, such problems should only hurt throughput,=
 not
> > > > lead to memory exhaustion.
